22class V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE ControlFlowBuilder {
23 public:
24 explicit ControlFlowBuilder(BytecodeArrayBuilder* builder)
25 : builder_(builder) {}
26 ControlFlowBuilder(const ControlFlowBuilder&) = delete;
27 ControlFlowBuilder& operator=(const ControlFlowBuilder&) = delete;
28 virtual ~ControlFlowBuilder() = default;
29
30 protected:
31 BytecodeArrayBuilder* builder() const { return builder_; }
32
33 private:
34 BytecodeArrayBuilder* builder_;
35};

37class V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE BreakableControlFlowBuilder
38 : public ControlFlowBuilder {
39 public:
40 BreakableControlFlowBuilder(BytecodeArrayBuilder* builder,
41 BlockCoverageBuilder* block_coverage_builder,
42 AstNode* node)
43 : ControlFlowBuilder(builder),
44 break_labels_(builder->zone()),
45 node_(node),
46 block_coverage_builder_(block_coverage_builder) {}
47 ~BreakableControlFlowBuilder() override;
48
49 // This method is called when visiting break statements in the AST.
50 // Inserts a jump to an unbound label that is patched when the corresponding
51 // BindBreakTarget is called.
52 void Break() { EmitJump(&break_labels_); }
53 void BreakIfTrue(BytecodeArrayBuilder::ToBooleanMode mode) {
54 EmitJumpIfTrue(mode, &break_labels_);
55 }
56 void BreakIfFalse(BytecodeArrayBuilder::ToBooleanMode mode) {
57 EmitJumpIfFalse(mode, &break_labels_);
58 }
59 void BreakIfUndefined() { EmitJumpIfUndefined(&break_labels_); }
60 void BreakIfNull() { EmitJumpIfNull(&break_labels_); }
61 void BreakIfForInDone(Register index, Register cache_length) {
62 EmitJumpIfForInDone(&break_labels_, index, cache_length);
63 }
64
65 BytecodeLabels* break_labels() { return &break_labels_; }
66
67 protected:
68 void EmitJump(BytecodeLabels* labels);
69 void EmitJumpIfTrue(BytecodeArrayBuilder::ToBooleanMode mode,
70 BytecodeLabels* labels);
71 void EmitJumpIfFalse(BytecodeArrayBuilder::ToBooleanMode mode,
72 BytecodeLabels* labels);
73 void EmitJumpIfUndefined(BytecodeLabels* labels);
74 void EmitJumpIfNull(BytecodeLabels* labels);
75 void EmitJumpIfForInDone(BytecodeLabels* labels, Register index,
76 Register cache_length);
77
78 // Called from the destructor to update sites that emit jumps for break.
79 void BindBreakTarget();
80
81 // Unbound labels that identify jumps for break statements in the code.
82 BytecodeLabels break_labels_;
83
84 // A continuation counter (for block coverage) is needed e.g. when
85 // encountering a break statement.
86 AstNode* node_;
87 BlockCoverageBuilder* block_coverage_builder_;
88};

101// A class to help with co-ordinating break and continue statements with
102// their loop.
103class V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE LoopBuilder final : public BreakableControlFlowBuilder {
104 public:
105 LoopBuilder(BytecodeArrayBuilder* builder,
106 BlockCoverageBuilder* block_coverage_builder, AstNode* node,
107 FeedbackVectorSpec* feedback_vector_spec)
108 : BreakableControlFlowBuilder(builder, block_coverage_builder, node),
109 continue_labels_(builder->zone()),
110 end_labels_(builder->zone()),
111 feedback_vector_spec_(feedback_vector_spec) {
112 if (block_coverage_builder_ != nullptr) {
113 block_coverage_body_slot_ =
114 block_coverage_builder_->AllocateBlockCoverageSlot(
115 node, SourceRangeKind::kBody);
116 }
117 source_position_ = node ? node->position() : kNoSourcePosition;
118 }
119 ~LoopBuilder() override;
120
121 void LoopHeader();
122 void LoopBody();
123 void JumpToHeader(int loop_depth, LoopBuilder* const parent_loop);
124 void BindContinueTarget();
125
126 // This method is called when visiting continue statements in the AST.
127 // Inserts a jump to an unbound label that is patched when BindContinueTarget
128 // is called.
129 void Continue() { EmitJump(&continue_labels_); }
130 void ContinueIfUndefined() { EmitJumpIfUndefined(&continue_labels_); }
131 void ContinueIfNull() { EmitJumpIfNull(&continue_labels_); }
132
133 private:
134 // Emit a Jump to our parent_loop_'s end label which could be a JumpLoop or,
135 // iff they are a nested inner loop with the same loop header bytecode offset
136 // as their parent's, a Jump to its parent's end label.
137 void JumpToLoopEnd() { EmitJump(&end_labels_); }
138 void BindLoopEnd();
139
140 BytecodeLoopHeader loop_header_;
141
142 // Unbound labels that identify jumps for continue statements in the code and
143 // jumps from checking the loop condition to the header for do-while loops.
144 BytecodeLabels continue_labels_;
145
146 // Unbound labels that identify jumps for nested inner loops which share the
147 // same header offset as this loop. Said inner loops will Jump to our end
148 // label, which could be a JumpLoop or, iff we are a nested inner loop too, a
149 // Jump to our parent's end label.
150 BytecodeLabels end_labels_;
151
152 int block_coverage_body_slot_;
153 int source_position_;
154 FeedbackVectorSpec* const feedback_vector_spec_;
155};

157// A class to help with co-ordinating break statements with their switch.
158class V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE SwitchBuilder final
159 : public BreakableControlFlowBuilder {
160 public:
161 SwitchBuilder(BytecodeArrayBuilder* builder,
162 BlockCoverageBuilder* block_coverage_builder,
163 SwitchStatement* statement, int number_of_cases,
164 BytecodeJumpTable* jump_table)
165 : BreakableControlFlowBuilder(builder, block_coverage_builder, statement),
166 case_sites_(builder->zone()),
167 default_(builder->zone()),
168 fall_through_(builder->zone()),
169 jump_table_(jump_table) {
170 case_sites_.resize(number_of_cases);
171 }
172
173 ~SwitchBuilder() override;
174
175 void BindCaseTargetForJumpTable(int case_value, CaseClause* clause);
176
177 void BindCaseTargetForCompareJump(int index, CaseClause* clause);
178
179 // This method is called when visiting case comparison operation for |index|.
180 // Inserts a JumpIfTrue with ToBooleanMode |mode| to a unbound label that is
181 // patched when the corresponding SetCaseTarget is called.
182 void JumpToCaseIfTrue(BytecodeArrayBuilder::ToBooleanMode mode, int index);
183
184 void EmitJumpTableIfExists(int min_case, int max_case,
185 std::map<int, CaseClause*>& covered_cases);
186
187 void BindDefault(CaseClause* clause);
188
189 void JumpToDefault();
190
191 void JumpToFallThroughIfFalse();
192
193 private:
194 // Unbound labels that identify jumps for case statements in the code.
195 ZoneVector<BytecodeLabel> case_sites_;
196 BytecodeLabels default_;
197 BytecodeLabels fall_through_;
198 BytecodeJumpTable* jump_table_;
199
200 void BuildBlockCoverage(CaseClause* clause) {
201 if (block_coverage_builder_ && clause != nullptr) {
202 block_coverage_builder_->IncrementBlockCounter(clause,
203 SourceRangeKind::kBody);
204 }
205 }
206};

271class V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE ConditionalChainControlFlowBuilder final
272 : public ControlFlowBuilder {
273 public:
274 ConditionalChainControlFlowBuilder(
275 BytecodeArrayBuilder* builder,
276 BlockCoverageBuilder* block_coverage_builder, AstNode* node,
277 size_t then_count)
278 : ControlFlowBuilder(builder),
279 end_labels_(builder->zone()),
280 then_count_(then_count),
281 then_labels_list_(static_cast<int>(then_count_), builder->zone()),
282 else_labels_list_(static_cast<int>(then_count_), builder->zone()),
283 block_coverage_then_slots_(then_count_, builder->zone()),
284 block_coverage_else_slots_(then_count_, builder->zone()),
285 block_coverage_builder_(block_coverage_builder) {
286 DCHECK(node->IsConditionalChain());
287
288 Zone* zone = builder->zone();
289 for (size_t i = 0; i < then_count_; ++i) {
290 then_labels_list_.Add(zone->New<BytecodeLabels>(zone), zone);
291 else_labels_list_.Add(zone->New<BytecodeLabels>(zone), zone);
292 }
293
294 if (block_coverage_builder != nullptr) {
295 ConditionalChain* conditional_chain = node->AsConditionalChain();
296 block_coverage_then_slots_.resize(then_count_);
297 block_coverage_else_slots_.resize(then_count_);
298 for (size_t i = 0; i < then_count_; ++i) {
299 block_coverage_then_slots_[i] =
300 block_coverage_builder->AllocateConditionalChainBlockCoverageSlot(
301 conditional_chain, SourceRangeKind::kThen, i);
302 block_coverage_else_slots_[i] =
303 block_coverage_builder->AllocateConditionalChainBlockCoverageSlot(
304 conditional_chain, SourceRangeKind::kElse, i);
305 }
306 }
307 }
308 ~ConditionalChainControlFlowBuilder() override;
309
310 BytecodeLabels* then_labels_at(size_t index) {
311 DCHECK_LT(index, then_count_);
312 return then_labels_list_[static_cast<int>(index)];
313 }
314
315 BytecodeLabels* else_labels_at(size_t index) {
316 DCHECK_LT(index, then_count_);
317 return else_labels_list_[static_cast<int>(index)];
318 }
319
320 int block_coverage_then_slot_at(size_t index) const {
321 DCHECK_LT(index, then_count_);
322 return block_coverage_then_slots_[index];
323 }
324
325 int block_coverage_else_slot_at(size_t index) const {
326 DCHECK_LT(index, then_count_);
327 return block_coverage_else_slots_[index];
328 }
329
330 void ThenAt(size_t index);
331 void ElseAt(size_t index);
332
333 void JumpToEnd();
334
335 private:
336 BytecodeLabels end_labels_;
337 size_t then_count_;
338 ZonePtrList<BytecodeLabels> then_labels_list_;
339 ZonePtrList<BytecodeLabels> else_labels_list_;
340
341 ZoneVector<int> block_coverage_then_slots_;
342 ZoneVector<int> block_coverage_else_slots_;
343 BlockCoverageBuilder* block_coverage_builder_;
344};
345
346class V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE ConditionalControlFlowBuilder final
347 : public ControlFlowBuilder {
348 public:
349 ConditionalControlFlowBuilder(BytecodeArrayBuilder* builder,
350 BlockCoverageBuilder* block_coverage_builder,
351 AstNode* node)
352 : ControlFlowBuilder(builder),
353 end_labels_(builder->zone()),
354 then_labels_(builder->zone()),
355 else_labels_(builder->zone()),
356 node_(node),
357 block_coverage_builder_(block_coverage_builder) {
358 DCHECK(node->IsIfStatement() || node->IsConditional());
359 if (block_coverage_builder != nullptr) {
360 block_coverage_then_slot_ =
361 block_coverage_builder->AllocateBlockCoverageSlot(
362 node, SourceRangeKind::kThen);
363 block_coverage_else_slot_ =
364 block_coverage_builder->AllocateBlockCoverageSlot(
365 node, SourceRangeKind::kElse);
366 }
367 }
368 ~ConditionalControlFlowBuilder() override;
369
370 BytecodeLabels* then_labels() { return &then_labels_; }
371 BytecodeLabels* else_labels() { return &else_labels_; }
372
373 void Then();
374 void Else();
375
376 void JumpToEnd();
377
378 private:
379 BytecodeLabels end_labels_;
380 BytecodeLabels then_labels_;
381 BytecodeLabels else_labels_;
382
383 AstNode* node_;
384 int block_coverage_then_slot_;
385 int block_coverage_else_slot_;
386 BlockCoverageBuilder* block_coverage_builder_;
387};
